line_1: Can, like Jack Shepherd, cut our fetters;
line_2: Thus, Sir, you see we men of letters

line_1: Thrust both legs; nor pull off the magical fetters,
line_2: Till you rise in the morn about family matters.

line_1: This makes us cramp our Sense in Fetters,
line_2: And teaze our Friends with chiming Letters.
